        // Early Life
        bio_early_life_title: "Early Life & Career",
        bio_early_life_subtitle1: "Personal Background",
        bio_early_life_p1: `Jason Aaron Peters was born in 1989 in Durban, a coastal city in the province of KwaZulu-Natal, South Africa, to Mark Giles Peters and Jill Diane Peters (née Holme). While his roots are in South Africa, his identity and professional trajectory were profoundly shaped by his upbringing in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia.`,
        bio_early_life_p2: `A long-term resident of Ethiopia for over 26 years, this cross-cultural experience provided him with a unique perspective, blending an external viewpoint with a deep, nuanced understanding of Ethiopian society. A foundational element of his professional identity is his deep cultural and linguistic integration, most evident in his fluency in Amharic. An interview with Addis out Media highlighted this, describing him as speaking the language "fluently" (using the Amharic phrase "ቅርጥፍጥፍ አርጓቷል," which conveys a high degree of natural proficiency).`,
        bio_early_life_p3: `This personal history is a cornerstone of his business strategy, allowing him to communicate complex technical concepts directly in Amharic and bypass cultural barriers. From an early age, Peters developed a keen interest in computers, specifically in foundational architecture and network infrastructure. This early focus on systemic thinking laid the groundwork for his future approach of building entire business ecosystems.`,
        bio_early_life_subtitle2: "Foundations in Media and Management (2008–2015)",
        bio_early_life_p4: `Peters' early professional life was characterized by demanding roles in management and media that collectively built his skills in business operations and public engagement.`,
        bio_early_life_p5: `His first major leadership role was as General Manager of <strong>Peters Industrial Enterprises PLC</strong> from 2008 to 2013. Immersed in the challenges of the industrial sector, his underlying passion for technology was evident. In 2011, he responded to a public call for the "Ubuntu Global Jam," confirming, "We Peters Industrial Enterprises PLC will be hosting the Ethiopian Jam." This action revealed his early efforts to cultivate a grassroots tech culture in Addis Ababa.`,
        bio_early_life_p6: `Concurrently, he embarked on a career that would define his public identity, joining <strong>105.3 Afro FM</strong> in June 2009. Over a six-year tenure, he held various roles, including presenter and producer, ultimately ascending to Program Manager. His time at Afro FM was a strategic immersion into the key demographic of tech early adopters. It was here that "JayP" became a recognized voice, building the public trust he would later leverage. Evidence also suggests he may have hosted "Rock 101 With Jason," described as "ETHIOPIA'S FIRST AND ONLY ROCK SHOW," indicating a long-term passion for broadcasting.`,
        bio_early_life_p7: `Further diversifying his skill set, Peters served as Manager at the <strong>Addis Regency Hotel</strong> from 2011 to 2012, sharpening his abilities in operational logistics and customer service.`,

        // Marketing
        bio_marketing_title: "Mastering Marketing and Advertising (2013–2021)",
        bio_marketing_p1: `For eight years, Peters served as General Partner and Marketing Director at <strong>Bunifu Advertising</strong>, a firm described as "Ethiopia's leading Creative Communications Team." This role was a crucial phase, providing the strategic framework to connect his content creation abilities with sustainable business models.`,
        bio_marketing_p2: `Operating in media (Afro FM until 2015) and advertising simultaneously, he created a professional feedback loop. He translated his practical understanding of audience engagement from radio into the commercial realm, developing brand strategies for businesses. This period honed his ability to think of content as a strategic asset and provided the final foundational piece before launching his own large-scale, tech-focused enterprises.`,
        
        // Media Ecosystem
        bio_media_title: `The Digital Vanguard: Building the "ETHIO TECH" Media Ecosystem`,
        bio_media_subtitle1: `"ETHIO TECH with JayP" YouTube Channel`,
        bio_media_p1: `The flagship of this ecosystem is the YouTube channel <strong>ETHIO TECH with JayP</strong>, founded in December 2019. The channel is explicitly branded in Amharic as "የኢትዮጵያ ቁጥር 1 የቴክኖሎጂ ቻናል" ("Ethiopia's number 1 technology channel"). As the sole creative force, JayP researches, edits, and presents all content, which ranges from tech reviews (e.g., Samsung Galaxy A12), and hardware projects (e.g., Raspberry Pi Zero W) to tutorials on digital marketing and making money online.`,
        bio_media_p2: `Analysis of the channel's content reveals a strategic evolution. While founded on general technology, its most popular and recent videos are heavily concentrated in FinTech, particularly cryptocurrency. Videos analyzing crypto-gaming platforms like Hamster Kombat have garnered exceptionally high view counts. This shift reflects a response to clear market demand, serving the dual purpose of capturing a highly motivated audience and cultivating a community receptive to his own FinTech ventures.`,
        bio_media_subtitle2: `"CYBER Ethiopia" Podcast and Broadcast`,
        bio_media_p3: `Complementing his YouTube presence, Peters hosts <strong>CYBER Ethiopia</strong>, a technology-focused podcast. The show is distributed on major platforms (Apple Podcasts, Spotify) and, significantly, is also broadcast as an "English Tech news Update" every Monday on <strong>104.7 EBC radio</strong>, a major state-affiliated broadcast outlet. This hybrid digital and traditional broadcast strategy allows him to reach diverse demographics, from digitally-native youth to a broader audience that relies on traditional radio.`,
        bio_media_subtitle3: `"ETHIO TECH NEWS"`,
        bio_media_p4: `In September 2021, Peters expanded his media presence by launching <strong>ETHIO TECH NEWS</strong>, assuming the role of Editor-in-Chief. This move elevated him from a content creator to a formal journalistic figure, further solidifying his brand's authority as a definitive source for industry developments.`,
        bio_media_subtitle4: `An Integrated Business Model`,
        bio_media_p5: `Peters has engineered a powerful, self-reinforcing cycle where his media influence directly drives technology adoption:`,
