        bio_media_li2: `<strong>Product Introduction:</strong> He introduces his own localized products (like The ETN Ecosystem) as superior, locally relevant alternatives.`,
        bio_media_li3: `<strong>Community Funneling:</strong> He directs his media audience to dedicated community channels (primarily Telegram) to encourage direct participation and adoption.`,
        bio_media_li4: `<strong>Content Reinforcement:</strong> The progress and successes within his ventures become new content for his media channels, serving as social proof and attracting new users into the funnel.`,

        // Ventures
        bio_ventures_title: "Entrepreneurial Ventures: Pioneering Ethiopian Technology",
        bio_ventures_subtitle1: "Ethio Tech AI and Maqdala-AI",
        bio_ventures_p1: `In December 2019, Peters founded <strong>Ethio Tech AI</strong>, recognized as Ethiopia's first artificial intelligence organization, predating the establishment of the national Ethiopian Artificial Intelligence Institute. The company's foundation was driven by what Peters described as outrage at the initial global launch of ChatGPT, which excluded Ethiopia and other African nations from creating accounts.`,
        bio_ventures_p2: `Viewing this regional lockout as a form of "technological fascism," Peters and a small group of engineers embarked on a workaround. They utilized thousands of temporary numbers from Western countries to create over 1,000 ChatGPT accounts. With the combined $20 sign-up credit from each account, they built a front-end, initially called ETHIO TECH GPT and later Magdala AI.`,
        bio_ventures_p3: `This initial version was massively successful, amassing over 100,000 daily active users at its peak. When the API credits were exhausted, the team realized they possessed a highly valuable asset: a large database of user questions and model answers. This database provided more than sufficient training data, which was subsequently used on Google's Vertex AI to build the proprietary, second-generation model that is today known as <strong>Maqdala-AI</strong>.`,
        bio_ventures_p4: `The company's flagship project, Maqdala-AI, is now a pioneering Large Language Model (LLM) focused on Ethiopian languages, marketed as a superior, locally-focused alternative "Advanced beyond ChatGPT" for Amharic and Afan Oromo.`,
        bio_ventures_p5: `The choice of the name "Maqdala" is a powerful act of cultural branding. Maqdala was the 19th-century mountain fortress of Emperor Tewodros II. Its siege by the British in 1868 and the subsequent looting of thousands of sacred manuscripts represent a profound cultural loss—a historical "data breach" of Ethiopian knowledge. By naming his Ethiopian-language LLM "Maqdala-AI," Peters frames its creation as the rebuilding of a national fortress of knowledge in the digital realm, a symbolic reclamation of cultural and digital sovereignty.`,
        bio_ventures_subtitle2: "Ge'ez eSport",
        bio_ventures_p6: `In October 2020, Peters co-founded <strong>Ge'ez eSport</strong>, serving as a Founding Member and Chief Technology Officer (CTO). The company enters a rapidly expanding Ethiopian gaming market. The branding is another example of cultural embedding. "Ge'ez" is the ancient liturgical language of Ethiopia, the foundation for Amharic and Tigrinya. By naming an eSports venture after Ge'ez, Peters imbues the modern world of competitive gaming with a sense of ancient heritage and national prestige.`,
